name: Plank
execution: Start in a push-up position with your elbows bent 90 degrees and your weight resting on your forearms
Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels, engaging your core muscles
Hold this position for the desired amount of time, keeping your core tight and avoiding sagging or arching

name: Russian Twists
execution: Sit on the floor with your knees bent and your feet elevated off the ground, leaning back slightly
Hold a weight plate or medicine ball with both hands at chest level
Exhale and rotate your torso to the right, bringing the weight towards the floor outside your right hip
Inhale and return to the starting position, then repeat on the left side

name: Leg Raises
execution: Hang from a pull-up bar or support yourself on dip bars with your arms straight
Exhale and raise your legs until they are parallel to the ground or higher
Inhale and lower your legs back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Crunches
execution: Lie on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor
Place your hands behind your head or across your chest
Exhale and lift your upper body off the floor, bringing your ribcage towards your pelvis
Inhale and lower your upper body back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Bicycle Crunches
execution: Lie on your back with your knees bent and your hands behind your head
Exhale and lift your shoulder blades off the floor, bringing your right elbow towards your left knee while straightening your right leg
Inhale and return to the starting position, then repeat on the other side
Continue alternating sides in a pedaling motion

name: Dead Bug
execution: Lie on your back with your arms extended towards the ceiling and your legs bent at a 90-degree angle
Exhale and extend your right leg towards the floor while simultaneously lowering your left arm overhead
Inhale and return to the starting position, then repeat with the opposite arm and leg
Continue alternating sides while keeping your lower back pressed into the floor

name: Plank with Shoulder Taps
execution: Start in a plank position with your elbows bent 90 degrees and your weight resting on your forearms
Exhale and tap your right shoulder with your left hand, then return to the starting position
Inhale and tap your left shoulder with your right hand, then return to the starting position
Continue alternating shoulder taps while keeping your core stable and avoiding rotation

name: Flutter Kicks
execution: Lie on your back with your legs extended and your hands under your glutes for support
Exhale and lift your legs a few inches off the ground
Alternately kick your legs up and down in a small, fluttering motion
Keep your core engaged and your lower back pressed into the floor throughout the movement

name: Mountain Climbers
execution: Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line from head to heels
Exhale and drive one knee towards your chest, then quickly switch legs
Continue alternating legs in a running motion while keeping your core engaged and your hips level
Maintain a steady pace throughout the exercise

name: Side Plank
execution: Lie on your side with your legs extended and your elbow directly beneath your shoulder
Exhale and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from head to heels
Engage your core muscles and hold this position for the desired amount of time
Repeat on the other side

name: Hanging Leg Raises
execution: Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms straight and your legs together
Exhale and raise your legs until they are parallel to the ground or higher
Inhale and lower your legs back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Squat Jumps
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart
Lower into a squat position, keeping your chest up and your knees behind your toes
Explosively jump upward, extending your hips, knees, and ankles fully
Land softly, bending your knees to absorb the impact, and immediately go into the next repetition

name: Box Jumps
execution: Stand facing a sturdy box or plyo box with your feet shoulder-width apart
Lower into a quarter squat position, swinging your arms behind you
Explosively jump onto the box, extending your hips, knees, and ankles fully
Land softly on the box with your knees slightly bent, then step or jump back down and repeat

name: Agility Ladder Drills
execution: Set up an agility ladder on the ground and stand at one end
Perform various footwork patterns through the ladder, such as high knees, lateral shuffles, and crossover steps
Focus on moving quickly and accurately, keeping your core engaged and your movements controlled
Repeat for several sets or time intervals

name: Medicine Ball Throws
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball at chest level
Lower into a quarter squat position, then explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles
Throw the medicine ball overhead or against a wall with maximum force, using your entire body
Catch the ball or retrieve it and repeat for the desired number of repetitions or time

name: Sprints
execution: Find an open space such as a track or field
Run as fast as you can for a specific distance or time interval
Focus on driving your knees up and pumping your arms for maximum speed
Rest and repeat for multiple sets or intervals

name: Pull-ups
execution: Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and palms facing away
Engage your back muscles and pull yourself up until your chin is over the bar
Lower yourself back down with control until your arms are fully extended
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions

name: Push-ups
execution: Start in a plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line from head to heels
Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides
Push yourself back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions

name: Boxing
execution: Put on boxing gloves and stand in front of a punching bag or partner
Perform a series of punches and combinations, such as jabs, crosses, hooks, and uppercuts
Move around the bag or your partner, using footwork to evade punches and change angles
Maintain a fast pace and focus on proper technique throughout the workout

name: Plyometric Push-ups
execution: Start in a plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart
Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows
Explosively push yourself up with enough force to lift your hands off the ground
Catch yourself and immediately lower back into the next repetition
Focus on explosiveness and power throughout the movement

name: Lateral Bounds
execution: Stand with your feet together and knees slightly bent
Push off with one foot and leap sideways as far as you can, landing softly on the opposite foot
Immediately push off in the opposite direction, using your arms to generate momentum
Continue bounding laterally back and forth for the desired number of repetitions or time

name: Burpees
execution: Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart
Lower into a squat position and place your hands on the ground in front of you
Kick your feet back into a plank position, perform a push-up, and then jump your feet back to the squat position
Explosively jump upwards, reaching your arms overhead
Land softly and immediately go into the next repetition

name: Lat Pulldown - Cable
execution: Exhale and pull the bar down in front of you to chest level
Squeeze your shoulder blades together and hold for a few seconds
Inhale, return to the starting position and repeat

name: Seated Cable Row
execution: Exhale and pull the handles towards your waist
Squeeze your shoulder blades together and hold for a few seconds
Inhale, return to the starting position and repeat

name: Deadlift - Barbell
execution: Keep your back straight, bend at the hips and knees to squat down and grab the bar
Exhale, straighten your legs and lift the bar, keeping it close to your body
Inhale and lower the bar to the ground and repeat

name: T-Bar Row
execution: Bend your knees slightly and keep your back straight, leaning forward from the waist
Exhale and pull the bar towards your chest
Inhale, return to the starting position and repeat

name: Pull-Up
execution: Grip the bar with palms facing away from you, wider than shoulder width
Exhale and pull yourself up until your chin is over the bar
Inhale and lower yourself back down and repeat

name: Single-Arm Dumbbell Row
execution: Place your right knee and right hand on the bench, left foot on the ground, and hold a dumbbell in your left hand
Exhale and lift the dumbbell to your side, keeping your elbow close to your body
Inhale and lower the dumbbell and repeat. Switch sides after the set

name: Back Extension
execution: Lie face down on the bench, with your ankles secured under the foot pads
Exhale and lift your torso up until your body forms a straight line
Inhale and lower your body back down and repeat

name: Bent Over Row - Barbell
execution: Bend your knees slightly and bend over the bar with your back straight
Exhale and pull the bar towards your waist
Inhale, lower the bar and repeat

name: Hyperextension
execution: Position yourself face down on the hyperextension bench with your thighs on the pad and your feet secured
Cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your head
Exhale and lift your torso until it's in line with your legs, squeezing your glutes and lower back
Inhale, lower your torso back to the starting position, and repeat

name: Seated Machine Row
execution: Sit on the machine with your chest against the pad and grip the handles
Exhale and pull the handles towards your abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together
Inhale, extend your arms back to the starting position, and repeat

name: Reverse Fly - Dumbbell
execution: Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other
Lean forward from the hips, keeping your back flat and arms hanging straight down
Exhale and raise the dumbbells out to the sides until they reach shoulder level, squeezing your shoulder blades together
Inhale, lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, and repeat

name: Barbell Curl
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip
Exhale and curl the barbell towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body
Inhale and lower the barbell back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip
Exhale and curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, keeping your palms facing each other
Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Preacher Curl - Machine
execution: Sit at the preacher curl machine with your upper arms resting on the pad and your chest against the pad
Exhale and curl the bar towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows stationary
Inhale and lower the bar back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Concentration Curl - Dumbbell
execution: Sit on a bench with your legs apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand
Rest the back of your upper arm on your inner thigh and fully extend your arm
Exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder, keeping your elbow stationary
Inhale and lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, keeping control

name: EZ-Bar Preacher Curl
execution: Sit at the preacher curl bench with your upper arms resting on the pad and your chest against the pad
Hold the EZ-bar with an underhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart
Exhale and curl the bar towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows stationary
Inhale and lower the bar back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Incline Dumbbell Curl
execution: Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended and palms facing up
Exhale and curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body
Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Cable Curl - Straight Bar
execution: Stand in front of a cable machine with a straight bar attached to the low pulley
Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart
Exhale and curl the bar towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body
Inhale and lower the bar back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Reverse Curl - Barbell
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart
Exhale and curl the bar towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body
Inhale and lower the bar back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Seated Alternating Dumbbell Curl
execution: Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended and palms facing up
Exhale and curl one dumbbell towards your shoulder while keeping the other arm fully extended
Inhale and lower the dumbbell back to the starting position, keeping control
Alternate between arms

name: Spider Curl - EZ-Bar
execution: Kneel facing a preacher curl bench, resting your upper arms on the pad and your chest against it
Hold the EZ-bar with an underhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart
Exhale and curl the bar towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows stationary
Inhale and lower the bar back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Standing Cable Curl
execution: Stand in front of a cable machine with a straight bar attached to the low pulley
Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart
Exhale and curl the bar towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body
Inhale and lower the bar back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Bench Fly - Cable
execution: Exhale and pull the bars up in an arc motion in front of your chest
Squeeze your chest and hold for a few seconds
Inhale, return to the starting position and repeat

name: Bench Fly - Dumbell
execution: Exhale and pull the dumbells up in an arc motion in front of your chest
Squeeze your chest and hold for a few seconds
Inhale, return to the starting position and repeat

name: Bench Press - Barbell
execution: Exhale and squeeze your chest to push the bar up to extend your arms straight.
Inhale and slowly lower the bar to the starting position and repeat

name: Decline Bench Press - Barbell
execution: Exhale and squeeze your chest to push the bar up to extend your arms straight.
Inhale and slowly lower the bar to the starting position and repeat

name: Flat Around the World - Dumbell
execution: Inhale and move dumbells in semi-circle to reach above your head
Exhale and bring dumbells back to the preperation position and repeat

name: Incline Bech Press-BArbell
execution: Exhale and squeeze your chest to push the bar up to extend your arms straight
Inhale and slowly lower your bar to just above your chest and repeat

name: Incline Pushups
execution: Inhale and lower your body down util your chest almost touches the bench or Floor if Flat Pushups
Exhale and Raise your Body back to the starting position and repeat

name: Pullover Dumbell
execution: Inhale to lower your arms behind your head until your arms are in line with your torso.
Streach out your chest and pause for a few seconds

name: Seated Chest Fly - Machine
execution: Exhale, and squeez your chest and press the handles together as close as possible
Pause for a few seconds, inahle and return tot he starting positio slowly and repeat

name: Seated Chest Press - Machine
execution: Exhale, and squeez your chest to push the handles away from you to extend your arms straight
Inhale and return tot he starting position slowly and repeat

name: Chest Dip
execution: Bend your elbows and tilt forward to lower yourself until your upper arms are parallel to the floor
Pause for a few seconds and push yourself up to the starting position slowly and repeat

name: Squats - Barbell
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell on your upper back
Lower your body by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight
Exhale and push through your heels to return to the starting position

name: Deadlifts - Barbell
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell in front of you on the ground
Bend at your hips and knees to lower your body and grip the bar with an overhand grip
Exhale, push through your heels, and lift the bar by straightening your hips and knees

name: Leg Press - Machine
execution: Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and feet shoulder-width apart on the platform
Push through your heels to extend your legs, lifting the weight
Lower the weight by bending your knees until they are at a 90-degree angle

name: Lunges - Dumbbell
execution: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding dumbbells by your sides
Step forward with one leg and lower your body until both knees are bent at 90 degrees
Push through your front heel to return to the starting position and repeat on the other leg

name: Calf Raises - Machine
execution: Stand on the machine with the balls of your feet on the platform and your shoulders under the pads
Push through the balls of your feet to raise your heels as high as possible
Lower your heels back down and repeat

name: Leg Curls - Machine
execution: Lie face down on the machine with your legs straight and your heels under the padded lever
Exhale and curl your legs up towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstrings
Inhale and slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position

name: Step-Ups
execution: Hold dumbbells by your sides and stand in front of the step box
Step onto the box with one foot, pushing through your heel to lift your body up
Step down with the same foot and repeat on the other side

name: Leg Extensions - Machine
execution: Sit on the machine with your knees bent at 90 degrees and the pad against your shins
Exhale and straighten your legs, lifting the weight
Inhale and slowly lower the weight back down to the starting position

name: Hack Squat - Machine
execution: Position yourself on the machine with your shoulders under the pads and your feet shoulder-width apart
Release the safety handles and lower yourself into a squat position
Push through your heels to straighten your legs and return to the starting position

name: Romanian Deadlift - Barbell
execution: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding the barbell in front of your thighs with an overhand grip
Keeping your back straight, hinge at your hips and lower the barbell towards the ground, sliding it down your legs
Exhale and squeeze your hamstrings and glutes to return to the starting position

name: Bulgarian Split Squats
execution: Stand about two feet in front of a bench with a dumbbell in each hand
Place one foot behind you on the bench, shoelaces down
Lower your body until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your torso upright
Push through your front heel to return to the starting position

name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press
execution: Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward
Exhale and press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended
Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Barbell Military Press
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at shoulder level with an overhand grip
Exhale and press the barbell overhead until your arms are fully extended
Inhale and lower the barbell back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Lateral Raises - Dumbbell
execution: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inward
Exhale and raise the dumbbells to the sides until they are parallel to the ground
Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Front Raises - Dumbbell
execution: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down
Exhale and raise the dumbbells in front of you until they are parallel to the ground
Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Bent Over Reverse Fly - Dumbbell
execution: Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back flat and knees slightly bent
Hold a dumbbell in each hand with palms facing each other
Exhale and raise the dumbbells to the sides until your arms are parallel to the ground
Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Upright Rows - Barbell
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip, hands closer than shoulder-width apart
Exhale and raise the barbell towards your chin, keeping it close to your body
Inhale and lower the barbell back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Arnold Press
execution: Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing towards you
Start with the dumbbells at shoulder height, elbows bent, and palms facing you
Exhale and press the dumbbells overhead while rotating your palms to face forward
Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, reversing the palm rotation
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions

name: Shrugs - Barbell
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip
Exhale and raise your shoulders towards your ears, contracting your traps
Inhale and lower your shoulders back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Reverse Fly - Machine
execution: Sit at the rear delt machine with your chest against the pad and your arms extended in front of you
Exhale and pull the handles apart until your arms are parallel to the ground
Inhale and return to the starting position, keeping control

name: Front Plate Raise
execution: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a weight plate with both hands in front of your thighs
Exhale and raise the weight plate in front of you until it is at shoulder height
Inhale and lower the weight plate back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Dumbbell Lateral Raises on Incline Bench
execution: Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms hanging down
Exhale and raise the dumbbells to the sides until they are parallel to the ground
Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Tricep Dips
execution: Start by supporting yourself on parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body vertical
Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground
Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms

name: Tricep Rope Pushdown
execution: Stand in front of a cable machine with a rope attachment at chest height
Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart
Exhale and extend your arms downward, squeezing your triceps at the bottom
Inhale and return to the starting position, keeping control

name: Skull Crushers - EZ-Bar
execution: Lie on a bench with an EZ-bar in your hands, arms extended vertically above your chest
Bend your elbows to lower the bar towards your forehead, keeping your upper arms stationary
Exhale and extend your arms back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Overhead Tricep Extension - Dumbbell
execution: Stand or sit with a dumbbell in one hand, arm extended overhead
Bend your elbow to lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your upper arm stationary
Exhale and extend your arm back to the starting position, keeping control

name: Tricep Kickbacks - Dumbbell
execution: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand and lean forward at the hips
Keep your upper arms close to your body and extend your forearms back until your arms are straight
Exhale and squeeze your triceps, then return to the starting position with control

name: Close Grip Bench Press
execution: Lie on a flat bench with a barbell, hands closer than shoulder-width apart
Lower the barbell to your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body
Exhale and press the barbell back up to the starting position, keeping control

name: Tricep Pushdown - Straight Bar
execution: Stand in front of a cable machine with a straight bar attached to the high pulley
Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart
Exhale and extend your arms downward, squeezing your triceps at the bottom
Inhale and return to the starting position, keeping control

name: Diamond Push-Ups
execution: Get into a push-up position with your hands close together, forming a diamond shape with your index fingers and thumbs
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the ground
Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms

name: Tricep Overhead Extension - Cable
execution: Stand facing away from the cable machine with a rope attachment at the high pulley
Grasp the rope with both hands behind your head, elbows bent
Exhale and extend your arms overhead, squeezing your triceps at the bottom
Inhale and return to the starting position, keeping control

name: Tricep Bench Dips
execution: Sit on the edge of a bench with your hands gripping the edge, fingers pointing forward
Walk your feet forward until your knees are at a 90-degree angle
Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground
Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms

name: Tricep Cable Kickbacks
execution: Stand facing the cable machine with a single handle attachment at the low pulley
Grasp the handle with one hand and extend your arm behind you
Exhale and fully extend your arm backward, squeezing your triceps at the top
Inhale and return to the starting position, keeping control
